Deluxe room
HOTEL & ACCOMMODATION IN CENTRAL VARBERG
Our hotel is located right in the heart of Varberg, on the west coast of Sweden. A truly unique hotel offering a whole range of package deals, experiences and an exciting Asian spa. Many of our guests are astounded and amazed when they step into the lobby of our beloved Varbergs Stadshotell with hotel traditions dating back to 1902. A place where evocative turn-of-the-century atmosphere intermingles with thousand-year-old influences from the Far East.
Book a room
Our special offers
Our hotel rooms
Enjoy first-class hotel accommodation close to the sea in Varberg
At Varbergs Stadshotell & Asia Spa we have hotel rooms to suit most tastes and preferences. Choose between our three categories: Boutique, Classic and Deluxe. A fusion between quaint turn-of-the-century design and the latest mod cons. Why not try a boutique room when you book your next stay with us? We promise your stay will be something out of the ordinary.
Classic
Our classic rooms represent a slightly more traditional alternative, boasting a very high standard and comfort. Beautiful wooden flooring and all the latest mod cons.
FIND OUT MORE ABOUT OUR CLASSIC ROOMS ›
Boutique
In our 66 boutique rooms, you will find innovative approaches and unique design features such as round beds or a bespoke bathtub in the middle of the room.
FIND OUT MORE ABOUT OUR BOUTIQUE ROOMS  ›
Deluxe
Our deluxe rooms have been recreated and lovingly restored to their former glory as they would have looked back in 1902. Turn-of-the-century romantic design combined with classic luxury and the latest modern comforts.
FIND OUT MORE ABOUT OUR DELUXE ROOMS ›
Facilities
Our facilities are available to all our hotel guests.
Relaxing at our hotel
Our relaxation lounge is separate to Asia Spa and here you will find a large, comfy sofa, a steam room, sauna, tropical rainforest shower and changing rooms with normal showers.  Available to all our guests.
Gym
The gym is located next to Asia Spa and is equipped with top-of-the-range kinesis stations, which helps you incorporate both aerobic exercises and muscular strength. Opening hours are 6 am to 10 pm, over 15s only.
Our hotel
This grand edifice that accommodates Varbergs Stadshotell & Asia Spa has been located here by the square since 1902.
The square in front of our hotel
There is a market taking place every Wednesday and Saturday, all year around. Literally on our doorstep.
Kallbadhuset - The local open-air seawater baths
Kallbadhuset and the little beach called 'Barnens badstrand' is situated just a couple of hundred metres from the hotel. A real, picturesque gem you when you visit Varberg.
Varberg Fortress
Originally built as a citadel in the 13th century and then enlarged towards the end of the 16th century to form a strong fortress, one of the most modern in Europe at the time.
The seafront promenade
The seafront promenade winds its way 2.4 kilometres from Varberg Fortress, along the seafront and all the way down to Lilla Apelviken. Enjoy the stunning scenery and salty breeze!
Relaxing at our hotel
Our relaxation lounge is separate to Asia Spa and here you will find a large, comfy sofa, a steam room, sauna, showers and changing rooms. Available to all our guests.
Dining at our hotel - Lobby menu
Take a seat in the hotel lobby, sit back and order something to nibble on or something to quench your thirst. Served daily between 4 pm - 10 pm.
Welcome to our hotel!
Come and experience our hotel and the fantastic surroundings in and around Varberg.
See our special offers ›
GLORIOUS VARBERG
THE WEST COAST AND SWEDEN MEET THE REST OF THE WORLD, RIGHT IN THE HEART OF VARBERG
Our hotel is located in Varberg town centre and right outside our lobby, a whole range of cultural activities and shopping await. Every Wednesday and Saturday, all-year round without fail, there is a market organised in the town square with plenty of stall holders selling their wares. Furthermore, we are no more than a short stroll away from the seafront and the harbour, and to walk around Varberg Fortress is truly fascinating regardless of the time of year. Spring, summer, autumn or winter, the stunning scenery and historic building never cease to amaze visitors.
Find to us
Read more about us
